1
00:00:39,740 --> 00:00:42,020
Let me ask you a question first.

2
00:00:42,020 --> 00:00:45,910
Where were you on the day when
Han Yoo-ra died?

3
00:00:45,910 --> 00:00:47,950
How did you get on the cruise?

4
00:00:47,950 --> 00:00:50,600
You didn’t even get the invitation.

5
00:00:51,230 --> 00:00:52,370
You are really the murderer!

6
00:00:52,370 --> 00:00:54,280
Hey!

7
00:00:54,280 --> 00:00:56,400
Mr. Do Min-joon!

8
00:00:57,340 --> 00:01:00,340
Hey! Do Min-joon!

9
00:01:00,340 --> 00:01:01,820
Hey! Do Min-joon!

10
00:01:01,820 --> 00:01:04,360
Hey! Do Min-joon!

11
00:01:05,860 --> 00:01:09,680
Hey! Stop there! Stop!

12
00:01:11,890 --> 00:01:13,650
Please don’t follow me.

13
00:01:13,650 --> 00:01:16,700
The guards are chasing me.

14
00:01:18,020 --> 00:01:22,360
Please go back to where you’re from.

15
00:01:23,070 --> 00:01:24,920
I…

16
00:01:29,950 --> 00:01:32,759
I said I would protect you.

17
00:01:38,820 --> 00:01:40,630
I…

18
00:01:42,390 --> 00:01:44,450
I don’t want to see you get hurt.

19
00:01:45,970 --> 00:01:51,759
So… Let’s go together.

20
00:02:08,080 --> 00:02:10,850
Hey! Stop there!

21
00:02:36,010 --> 00:02:38,890
[My Love from the Star Record 6]

22
00:02:39,840 --> 00:02:42,040
Those journalists came in a crowd.

23
00:02:42,040 --> 00:02:44,760
How can we stop them?

24
00:02:49,100 --> 00:02:50,810
Who are you?

25
00:02:53,460 --> 00:02:56,240
Well, I…

26
00:02:56,240 --> 00:03:00,330
I live here. Room 2302.

27
00:03:01,440 --> 00:03:03,830
Looks like you have just been on this job.

28
00:03:03,830 --> 00:03:06,210
The former staffs know me.

29
00:03:06,210 --> 00:03:09,000
Well, thank you.

30
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:10,430
Have you ever seen him before?

31
00:03:10,430 --> 00:03:11,820
No.

32
00:03:11,820 --> 00:03:16,510
He seemed to fall from the sky.

33
00:03:16,510 --> 00:03:18,050
Wait!

34
00:03:18,050 --> 00:03:19,980
Stop!

35
00:03:22,940 --> 00:03:26,380
What tea do you like? I got some good tea.

36
00:03:26,380 --> 00:03:29,790
It came a long way here from Costa Rica…

37
00:03:30,300 --> 00:03:32,960
But there isn’t any left.

38
00:03:32,960 --> 00:03:36,130
Do you like instant coffee?

39
00:03:36,130 --> 00:03:40,170
It’s also great to have a cup of instant coffee
in such a rainy day.

40
00:04:13,350 --> 00:04:15,610
What are you doing here?

41
00:04:17,490 --> 00:04:21,010
I'd like to see
what the actress's evening dresses looks like.

42
00:04:21,010 --> 00:04:23,200
Sorry for my rudeness.

43
00:04:24,360 --> 00:04:26,280
Let’s enjoy the coffee.

44
00:04:33,290 --> 00:04:36,260
Are you… alright?

45
00:04:36,260 --> 00:04:36,990
What?

46
00:04:36,990 --> 00:04:42,220
There are many rumors about Han Yoo-ra.

47
00:04:45,230 --> 00:04:48,350
Jae-kyung… Are you OK with that?

48
00:04:48,350 --> 00:04:50,500
What?

49
00:04:50,500 --> 00:04:52,090
Why do you ask this?

50
00:04:52,090 --> 00:04:57,260
Actually, I know your relationship with Yoo-ra.

51
00:04:58,370 --> 00:05:02,580
You are going to announce your wedding, right?

52
00:05:04,730 --> 00:05:07,230
How do you know that?

53
00:05:08,440 --> 00:05:10,570
I heard that.

54
00:05:10,570 --> 00:05:12,090
What?

55
00:05:12,090 --> 00:05:14,560
I heard the talk between you two.

56
00:05:21,890 --> 00:05:25,900
What did you hear? How much of it?

57
00:05:25,900 --> 00:05:30,550
You had a quarrel in the restroom, right?

58
00:05:30,550 --> 00:05:34,570
Because of the announcement of your wedding.

59
00:05:34,570 --> 00:05:39,250
I can tell that you’ve been together for long.

60
00:05:39,250 --> 00:05:42,990
Have you told this to anyone else?

61
00:05:42,990 --> 00:05:46,909
No. Who can I tell this to?

62
00:05:46,909 --> 00:05:49,380
I’m just thinking that…

63
00:05:51,100 --> 00:05:53,360
You have that relationship with Yoo-ra.

64
00:05:53,360 --> 00:05:57,070
But she turned to be like that now.

65
00:05:57,070 --> 00:06:02,630
I’m afraid you will feel sad about the quarrel.

66
00:06:02,630 --> 00:06:04,980
I want to comfort you.

67
00:06:04,980 --> 00:06:09,750
Looks like you have heard all of it that day.

68
00:06:09,750 --> 00:06:13,420
It gets more troublesome.

69
00:06:13,420 --> 00:06:15,840
What?

70
00:06:15,840 --> 00:06:17,870
You said you have insomnia, right?

71
00:06:17,870 --> 00:06:20,020
How do you feel recently?

72
00:06:20,020 --> 00:06:23,550
It will be more serious when I get sensitive.

73
00:06:23,550 --> 00:06:26,690
I will have some sleeping pills then.

74
00:06:26,690 --> 00:06:28,650
Take care of yourself.

75
00:06:28,650 --> 00:06:32,820
I came when I think of Yoo-ra to be like that.

76
00:06:32,820 --> 00:06:35,050
Thank you, Jae-kyung.

77
00:06:39,830 --> 00:06:41,510
What? Why are you here?

78
00:06:41,510 --> 00:06:45,300
I haven't been able to get in touch with you…

79
00:06:47,190 --> 00:06:48,700
Who is here?

80
00:06:48,700 --> 00:06:50,870
Who is he?

81
00:06:50,870 --> 00:06:52,190
What?

82
00:06:52,190 --> 00:06:54,040
Is he the brat next door?

83
00:06:54,040 --> 00:06:55,710
I’m asking you!

84
00:06:55,710 --> 00:06:57,930
Your brother! Idiot.

85
00:06:57,930 --> 00:06:59,440
What?

86
00:07:00,790 --> 00:07:04,600
Jae-kyung?

87
00:07:04,600 --> 00:07:05,800
Why are you here?

88
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:09,300
I was visiting someone, and dropped by.

89
00:07:09,300 --> 00:07:12,190
Even if so, you are still a man.

90
00:07:12,190 --> 00:07:15,430
I can’t accept that you two stay together alone.

91
00:07:15,430 --> 00:07:17,270
Hey!

92
00:07:18,410 --> 00:07:21,390
I have seen my friend and checked her safety.

93
00:07:21,390 --> 00:07:22,900
I’m leaving now.

94
00:07:22,900 --> 00:07:24,020
OK, Jae-kyung.

95
00:07:24,020 --> 00:07:26,290
Remember to take him with you.

96
00:07:26,290 --> 00:07:28,480
I just came here!

97
00:07:28,480 --> 00:07:29,290
Jae-kyung, you can go back first

98
00:07:29,290 --> 00:07:32,340
and tell mom that I won’t go home…

99
00:07:38,800 --> 00:07:41,050
I’m sorry. It’s our job.

100
00:07:41,050 --> 00:07:46,040
You know, Cheon Song-yi asked for
more control of outsiders.

101
00:07:46,040 --> 00:07:48,030
The protests of the residents were like a river…

102
00:07:48,030 --> 00:07:48,870
Can I leave now?

103
00:07:48,870 --> 00:07:51,000
Yes. Of course.

104
00:08:15,700 --> 00:08:16,480
What happened?

105
00:08:16,480 --> 00:08:18,980
Why did all the lights on the stairs light up?

106
00:08:18,980 --> 00:08:20,170
Did anything go by there?

107
00:08:20,170 --> 00:08:22,780
Nothing can be that fast.

108
00:08:22,780 --> 00:08:24,490
Unless it’s a ghost.

109
00:08:24,490 --> 00:08:26,300
Maybe they are out of order.

110
00:08:26,300 --> 00:08:29,570
It’s scary.

111
00:08:38,320 --> 00:08:41,299
I need to thank you for that day in hospital.

112
00:08:41,299 --> 00:08:44,430
Thanks to you, I almost got beaten.

113
00:08:44,430 --> 00:08:45,580
Where is Cheon Song-yi?

114
00:08:45,580 --> 00:08:46,820
What?

115
00:08:46,820 --> 00:08:49,810
Where is Cheon Song-yi?

116
00:08:49,810 --> 00:08:51,230
Is she your friend?

117
00:08:51,230 --> 00:08:53,020
Your lover?

118
00:09:00,630 --> 00:09:04,050
You rang the doorbell just now?

119
00:09:04,050 --> 00:09:06,360
Song-yi!

120
00:09:06,360 --> 00:09:07,910
Song-yi! Open the door!

121
00:09:07,910 --> 00:09:12,000
Why did so many men come to me today?

122
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:13,680
Are you all right?

123
00:09:13,680 --> 00:09:15,310
What are you talking about?

124
00:09:15,310 --> 00:09:17,600
Hey! You boy next door!

125
00:09:17,600 --> 00:09:18,120
Open the door!

126
00:09:18,120 --> 00:09:21,470
Why is he outside?

127
00:09:21,470 --> 00:09:22,210
What’s wrong?

128
00:09:22,210 --> 00:09:24,930
Has anyone come to your house besides him?

129
00:09:24,930 --> 00:09:26,910
What? Jae-kyung?

130
00:09:26,910 --> 00:09:27,880
Who is that?

131
00:09:27,880 --> 00:09:30,690
The brother of the one who is knocking the door.

132
00:09:30,690 --> 00:09:33,140
Different from him, Jae-kyung is excellent.

133
00:09:33,140 --> 00:09:36,410
And he is the heir to S&C Group.

134
00:09:36,410 --> 00:09:38,760
Why do you ask this?

135
00:09:38,760 --> 00:09:40,310
Cheon Song-yi!

136
00:09:40,310 --> 00:09:42,200
Open the door! Cheon Song-yi!

137
00:09:42,200 --> 00:09:44,390
Hey! Brat! Open the door!

138
00:09:44,390 --> 00:09:45,950
Let me open the door first.

139
00:09:45,950 --> 00:09:47,990
Which woman

140
00:09:47,990 --> 00:09:50,250
will open the door to anyone?

141
00:09:50,250 --> 00:09:51,450
What?

142
00:09:51,450 --> 00:09:54,290
You don’t even know who they really are.

143
00:09:54,290 --> 00:09:57,750
How could a woman be so careless?

144
00:09:57,750 --> 00:09:59,380
You are right.

145
00:09:59,380 --> 00:10:02,830
I don’t even know what kind of man you are.

146
00:10:02,830 --> 00:10:04,030
How careless I am!

147
00:10:04,030 --> 00:10:06,230
I don’t mean me. All the other men except me.

148
00:10:06,230 --> 00:10:07,420
Why are you an exception?

149
00:10:07,420 --> 00:10:10,540
Get out! Now!

150
00:10:10,540 --> 00:10:12,940
Wait! I don’t like being touched by others.

151
00:10:12,940 --> 00:10:15,630
Save it.

152
00:10:18,780 --> 00:10:20,450
Song-yi, are you OK?

153
00:10:20,450 --> 00:10:21,800
Did he do anything bad to you?

154
00:10:21,800 --> 00:10:25,630
I’m not a man who will do that.

155
00:10:25,630 --> 00:10:27,370
I told you last time.

156
00:10:27,370 --> 00:10:29,660
You are just a jerk like how you look to be.

157
00:10:29,660 --> 00:10:31,270
I have really seen everything in my long life.

158
00:10:31,270 --> 00:10:32,880
It’s my first time to be described like this.

159
00:10:32,880 --> 00:10:34,920
No way. There must be many people who said that.

160
00:10:34,920 --> 00:10:37,950
Guys. I’m really tired today.

161
00:10:37,950 --> 00:10:39,810
Do me a favor. Go home.

162
00:10:39,810 --> 00:10:41,520
OK.

163
00:10:41,520 --> 00:10:42,790
You can leave now.

164
00:10:42,790 --> 00:10:44,120
So do you!

165
00:10:44,120 --> 00:10:46,490
Hey. We haven't seen each other for days.

166
00:10:46,490 --> 00:10:48,730
Just a cup of coffee…

167
00:10:51,840 --> 00:10:53,870
Hey, you.

168
00:10:53,870 --> 00:10:55,760
A word.

169
00:10:55,760 --> 00:10:57,690
I got something to ask you.

170
00:11:02,220 --> 00:11:06,010
Do you own that apartment?

171
00:11:06,010 --> 00:11:08,060
Or a rental? Monthly?

172
00:11:08,060 --> 00:11:09,220
Why are you asking this?

173
00:11:09,220 --> 00:11:10,970
If it’s your house, I want to buy it.

174
00:11:10,970 --> 00:11:13,440
Double price. How is it?

175
00:11:13,440 --> 00:11:17,640
I’ll leave if that’s all you want to say.

176
00:11:17,640 --> 00:11:21,420
I don’t know how you feel about Song-yi.

177
00:11:21,420 --> 00:11:25,080
But I hope you can give up.

178
00:11:25,080 --> 00:11:25,750
Why?

179
00:11:25,750 --> 00:11:30,820
Because, she is my woman.

180
00:11:30,820 --> 00:11:33,370
Your woman…

181
00:11:33,370 --> 00:11:37,160
Does she admit that?

182
00:11:38,840 --> 00:11:42,140
Well… She…

183
00:11:42,140 --> 00:11:44,210
Haven’t… yet.

184
00:11:44,210 --> 00:11:47,450
But she will, soon.

185
00:11:47,450 --> 00:11:51,840
I didn’t want to say this at the beginning.

186
00:11:51,840 --> 00:11:54,490
My relationship with her is special.

187
00:11:54,490 --> 00:11:56,490
I have been loving her since middle school.

188
00:11:56,490 --> 00:11:59,920
We went to tutoring class together.
I bought her flowers for graduation.

189
00:11:59,920 --> 00:12:03,150
Her first to drink was also with me.

190
00:12:03,150 --> 00:12:06,080
I did all these before.

191
00:12:06,080 --> 00:12:09,100
And I will do more things with her in future.

192
00:12:09,100 --> 00:12:12,140
I’ll take care of her in this life

193
00:12:12,140 --> 00:12:14,970
until we die.

194
00:12:14,970 --> 00:12:18,820
Jealousy is the lowest, clumsy and childish

195
00:12:18,820 --> 00:12:21,370
emotion among human feelings.

196
00:12:21,370 --> 00:12:26,850
Because this is from the fear that
the other’s love will turn to another people.

197
00:12:26,850 --> 00:12:29,590
This kind of emotion, like anger,

198
00:12:29,590 --> 00:12:32,000
starts in early childhood.

199
00:12:32,000 --> 00:12:35,080
When you see your mother
holding other children happily,

200
00:12:35,080 --> 00:12:37,930
you will have a bad temper,
spit out the finished food,

201
00:12:37,930 --> 00:12:41,050
or suck your fingers. That's an example.

202
00:12:41,050 --> 00:12:43,720
We usually call it degradation.

203
00:12:43,720 --> 00:12:45,910
Even when grown up,

204
00:12:45,910 --> 00:12:49,220
when people with weak self-esteem
fall in love with others,

205
00:12:49,220 --> 00:12:51,660
they will experience this degradation process,

206
00:12:51,660 --> 00:12:54,270
and they will express their feelings of jealousy

207
00:12:54,270 --> 00:12:56,840
by making clumsy behaviors and words

208
00:12:56,840 --> 00:13:00,420
in fear of lover being taken away by others.

209
00:13:01,450 --> 00:13:05,630
Professor, won’t you feel jealous
when you fall in love with someone?

210
00:13:06,480 --> 00:13:08,360
Did you hear me?

211
00:13:08,360 --> 00:13:10,560
So, don’t hang around

212
00:13:10,560 --> 00:13:12,280
Song-yi again in the future.

213
00:13:12,280 --> 00:13:13,850
I came to see her for some reason.

214
00:13:13,850 --> 00:13:15,800
What is it?

215
00:13:15,800 --> 00:13:20,590
She left a purple hair band in my home.

216
00:13:20,590 --> 00:13:22,310
I came here to tell her to take it back.

217
00:13:22,310 --> 00:13:24,730
What?

218
00:13:24,730 --> 00:13:28,050
Why did she leave that thing in your home?

219
00:13:28,050 --> 00:13:29,820
Did she get drunk and go to a wrong place again?

220
00:13:29,820 --> 00:13:34,590
No, not like that. Don’t get it wrong.

221
00:13:34,590 --> 00:13:38,010
She stayed in my place for one night in sober.

222
00:13:40,340 --> 00:13:43,630
Alas, I need to give it back to her now.

223
00:13:43,630 --> 00:13:45,270
You look very cool.

224
00:13:45,270 --> 00:13:48,160
So I think you will never feel jealous.

225
00:13:48,160 --> 00:13:49,830
Just like what I said,

226
00:13:49,830 --> 00:13:53,450
jealousy is the lowest and childish emotion.

227
00:13:53,450 --> 00:13:57,220
Only people with weak self-esteem will have that.

228
00:13:57,220 --> 00:13:59,220
So I have never felt jealous.

229
00:14:01,250 --> 00:14:03,480
The final exam will be next week.

230
00:14:03,480 --> 00:14:05,900
I hope everyone will present.

231
00:14:08,950 --> 00:14:10,250
Go away! Cheon Song-yi!

232
00:14:10,250 --> 00:14:12,220
You killed Yoo-ra! How cruel you are!

233
00:14:12,220 --> 00:14:13,970
What place do you think this is?

234
00:14:26,620 --> 00:14:28,650
Song-yi, we can do nothing now.

235
00:14:28,650 --> 00:14:32,000
Many journalists and Yoo-ra’s fans are out there.

236
00:14:32,000 --> 00:14:34,280
And the families of Yoo-ra won’t let us in.

237
00:14:35,730 --> 00:14:38,190
We’d better go back now.

238
00:14:39,950 --> 00:14:44,120
I want to return the things of Yoo-ra.

239
00:14:55,770 --> 00:14:59,000
What’s wrong? Anything happened?

240
00:15:01,090 --> 00:15:03,390
My daughter is hurt so much, can’t you see that?

241
00:15:03,390 --> 00:15:06,550
How did you deal with that as the agency?

242
00:15:07,320 --> 00:15:09,440
Say something!

243
00:15:09,440 --> 00:15:12,480
Madam, we also lost a lot for the matter.

244
00:15:12,480 --> 00:15:15,590
Weren’t the things you lost earned by Song-yi?

245
00:15:15,590 --> 00:15:17,820
What did you do when she earned you money?

246
00:15:17,820 --> 00:15:19,500
You said you wanted to work with her forever,

247
00:15:19,500 --> 00:15:21,590
and we are family.

248
00:15:21,590 --> 00:15:24,760
Now you got loss, so you want to get rid of us?

249
00:15:24,760 --> 00:15:27,130
Madam, madam,

250
00:15:27,130 --> 00:15:29,100
please calm down.

251
00:15:29,100 --> 00:15:33,510
The contract will expire at the end of this month.

252
00:15:33,510 --> 00:15:35,770
Gosh. So what?

253
00:15:38,280 --> 00:15:40,080
Oh, Song-yi is here.

254
00:15:40,080 --> 00:15:43,100
Let’s continue in front of her.

255
00:15:43,100 --> 00:15:46,450
The contract is going to expire, and then?

256
00:15:46,450 --> 00:15:49,130
So, we won’t renew the contract for now.

257
00:15:49,130 --> 00:15:50,670
That’s OK.

258
00:15:50,670 --> 00:15:52,740
-What?
-Hey!

259
00:15:55,070 --> 00:15:59,150
For old times' sake, I wanted to renew.

260
00:15:59,150 --> 00:16:04,840
But the way you handled the accident
was so terrible.

261
00:16:04,840 --> 00:16:07,740
That’s not good enough to be my agency.

262
00:16:08,540 --> 00:16:10,970
So, I have to consider that.

263
00:16:12,720 --> 00:16:13,730
Really?

264
00:16:13,730 --> 00:16:16,480
I will be responsible for the damages.

265
00:16:16,480 --> 00:16:19,510
Are you… really going to do this?

266
00:16:19,510 --> 00:16:20,850
Cheon Song-yi! What’s on your mind?

267
00:16:20,850 --> 00:16:22,380
Why are you responsible for this?

268
00:16:23,110 --> 00:16:25,460
Just deal with it according to the contract!

269
00:16:25,460 --> 00:16:27,960
I will have a long rest. Don’t disturb me.

270
00:16:27,960 --> 00:16:30,560
OK. Got it. Have a good rest.

271
00:16:31,490 --> 00:16:32,800
Don’t come with me.

272
00:16:32,800 --> 00:16:34,930
You are not my manager now.

273
00:16:46,020 --> 00:16:47,760
It’s great, isn’t it?

274
00:16:48,910 --> 00:16:50,100
Yes.

275
00:16:51,750 --> 00:16:53,700
She left here herself!

276
00:16:54,780 --> 00:16:57,010
Hey you! Are you insane?

277
00:16:57,010 --> 00:16:58,140
Do you know how much the damages are?

278
00:16:58,140 --> 00:16:59,780
Where will you get the money?

279
00:16:59,780 --> 00:17:01,210
They got the loss because of me.

280
00:17:01,210 --> 00:17:03,560
How could I put all the blame on President An?

281
00:17:04,690 --> 00:17:06,700
You make me feel strange.

282
00:17:06,700 --> 00:17:08,710
When did you become so kind?

283
00:17:08,710 --> 00:17:11,240
Can’t you be that kind to me?

284
00:17:11,240 --> 00:17:13,280
Now all the TV shows and commercials
are breaking off with you.

285
00:17:13,280 --> 00:17:16,020
Where can you get so much money?

286
00:17:23,030 --> 00:17:24,910
Se-mi, it’s been a while.

287
00:17:24,910 --> 00:17:26,859
What brings you here?

288
00:17:26,859 --> 00:17:30,040
We’re here to see President An.

289
00:17:30,040 --> 00:17:31,890
The TV play changed suddenly.

290
00:17:31,890 --> 00:17:34,230
So we got a lot of to prepare.

291
00:17:34,230 --> 00:17:37,740
Changed?

292
00:17:37,740 --> 00:17:39,560
Don’t you know that?

293
00:17:40,300 --> 00:17:42,350
The play has finished halfway.

294
00:17:42,350 --> 00:17:44,860
It’s hard to reselect the leading role.

295
00:17:44,860 --> 00:17:46,390
So the story was changed to that
after Song-yi goes abroad to study,

296
00:17:46,390 --> 00:17:49,760
Se-mi develops the relationship with the hero.

297
00:17:49,760 --> 00:17:50,820
What?

298
00:17:51,710 --> 00:17:55,190
Mom, don’t say that.

299
00:17:55,190 --> 00:17:58,160
Song-yi, don’t get me wrong.

300
00:17:58,160 --> 00:18:04,330
Director suggested like that. But I refused.

301
00:18:04,330 --> 00:18:06,840
What? Really?

302
00:18:07,470 --> 00:18:09,400
Yes, mom.

303
00:18:09,400 --> 00:18:11,100
Sorry that I didn’t tell you.

304
00:18:11,100 --> 00:18:14,050
I wanted to tell you before President An.

305
00:18:14,050 --> 00:18:15,840
What’s wrong with you?

306
00:18:17,470 --> 00:18:19,750
It’s such a rare chance for you!

307
00:18:19,750 --> 00:18:21,890
How can I do that?

308
00:18:22,840 --> 00:18:26,450
I can’t do that though it’s a rare chance.

309
00:18:27,100 --> 00:18:30,040
Song-yi was wronged.

310
00:18:30,040 --> 00:18:33,870
As her best friend, I can’t take her place.

311
00:18:35,480 --> 00:18:39,340
Only if I can wait, there will be another chance.

312
00:18:41,080 --> 00:18:45,770
I can do nothing if there is no chance for me.

313
00:18:46,840 --> 00:18:49,770
You are more reasonable than your mom.

314
00:18:50,730 --> 00:18:53,440
So, Song-yi, don’t worry.

315
00:18:53,440 --> 00:18:55,220
I’m here just to say this.

316
00:18:55,220 --> 00:18:56,470
You can do that.

317
00:18:57,720 --> 00:18:58,510
What?

318
00:18:58,510 --> 00:19:02,130
My place will be taken away anyway.

319
00:19:02,130 --> 00:19:06,540
I quit not because of you, but the situation now.

320
00:19:06,540 --> 00:19:08,390
So, just do what you like.

321
00:19:09,640 --> 00:19:10,800
That’s right.

322
00:19:11,510 --> 00:19:13,590
You are more reasonable than your mom.

323
00:19:15,030 --> 00:19:16,330
Even if you say that…

324
00:19:16,330 --> 00:19:19,000
It’s OK. Just do it.

325
00:19:19,990 --> 00:19:21,010
Song-yi…

326
00:19:21,010 --> 00:19:23,730
President An is waiting. Go now.

327
00:19:30,170 --> 00:19:34,800
Your mom broke her ankle.
Is it OK for her to wear high heels?

328
00:19:36,960 --> 00:19:39,390
What’s wrong? Whose message is that?

329
00:19:39,390 --> 00:19:42,960
It’s… my mom. She fell down on the ice.

330
00:19:42,960 --> 00:19:45,060
Her ankle was broken.

331
00:19:46,760 --> 00:19:49,550
What ankle?

332
00:19:49,550 --> 00:19:51,170
Broken?

333
00:19:58,470 --> 00:20:00,360
Is that real?

334
00:20:00,360 --> 00:20:03,510
Did you really say that to the director?

335
00:20:03,510 --> 00:20:06,610
Let’s go to see the director to explain.

336
00:20:06,610 --> 00:20:08,290
Don’t bother.

337
00:20:08,290 --> 00:20:10,180
I have promised him that I will do it.

338
00:20:10,180 --> 00:20:11,830
What?

339
00:20:11,830 --> 00:20:14,140
Then why did you…

340
00:20:14,140 --> 00:20:17,590
Yes, I lied just now.

341
00:20:17,590 --> 00:20:20,440
I feel guilty for Song-yi.

342
00:20:20,440 --> 00:20:23,680
I hope she can allow me to do that. So I lied.

343
00:20:23,680 --> 00:20:25,310
But, mom.

344
00:20:26,410 --> 00:20:28,440
You saw her face just now.

345
00:20:32,040 --> 00:20:34,870
It’s not a good expression.

346
00:20:36,100 --> 00:20:41,590
I have always been kind to her.

347
00:20:42,610 --> 00:20:48,720
Because she never treated you as a friend,
but her foil.

348
00:20:48,720 --> 00:20:52,030
So you have to try your best this time

349
00:20:52,030 --> 00:20:56,380
and let her know how it feels that
her foil becomes more popular.

350
00:21:20,860 --> 00:21:22,470
Do Min-joon!

351
00:21:22,470 --> 00:21:24,360
Do Min-joon! Aren’t you home?

352
00:21:37,760 --> 00:21:40,190
Why are you always away when I need you?

353
00:21:41,590 --> 00:21:43,270
Where did you go?

354
00:21:45,200 --> 00:21:47,760
He just disappeared.

355
00:21:47,760 --> 00:21:49,880
My innocent car was impounded.

356
00:21:49,880 --> 00:21:53,010
I even was fined for running a red light.

357
00:21:53,010 --> 00:21:57,050
I've never driven illegally in my life.

358
00:21:57,050 --> 00:22:00,270
The reference person can’t be brought back.

359
00:22:00,270 --> 00:22:02,250
Let's call him here in formal order.

360
00:22:02,250 --> 00:22:06,340
But, it’s really weird.

361
00:22:06,340 --> 00:22:11,860
He was right in front of me,
but he disappeared like a wisp of smoke.

362
00:22:11,860 --> 00:22:14,740
Maybe he ran into one of the buildings.

363
00:22:14,740 --> 00:22:17,260
But the time is really limited.

364
00:22:18,420 --> 00:22:20,380
Is it that…

365
00:22:20,380 --> 00:22:26,070
Think about it. He also disappeared in the CCTV.

366
00:22:26,070 --> 00:22:27,560
Does he…

367
00:22:29,710 --> 00:22:31,130
Have superpower?

368
00:22:33,410 --> 00:22:34,880
Mr. Park…

369
00:22:34,880 --> 00:22:35,970
Fine.

370
00:22:35,970 --> 00:22:38,860
I must be confused by the rain yesterday.

371
00:22:40,310 --> 00:22:44,160
Who on earth is that guy?

372
00:22:44,160 --> 00:22:46,490
I have done some research about him.

373
00:22:46,490 --> 00:22:47,990
He is really not a normal person.

374
00:22:47,990 --> 00:22:49,170
Really?

375
00:22:49,170 --> 00:22:53,530
He has a surprising fortune.

376
00:22:54,810 --> 00:22:57,020
He can be called a zillionaire.

377
00:23:04,790 --> 00:23:06,180
Got it!

378
00:23:16,200 --> 00:23:18,670
I first sort out his real estates.

379
00:23:18,670 --> 00:23:21,080
It surprised me a lot when I did that.

380
00:23:21,080 --> 00:23:23,770
How did you invest it?

381
00:23:23,770 --> 00:23:26,120
I have been living for more than 400 years.

382
00:23:26,120 --> 00:23:28,680
Of course, I have saved so much.

383
00:23:28,680 --> 00:23:31,370
Was your family an official before?

384
00:23:31,370 --> 00:23:33,570
Why do you have so many houses in Kangnam?

385
00:23:33,570 --> 00:23:38,390
I stated to invest real estates in 1753.

386
00:23:39,210 --> 00:23:44,400
A man called Yun Seong-dong
was a famous agent in Hanyang.

387
00:23:47,870 --> 00:23:49,710
That way.

388
00:23:49,710 --> 00:23:51,070
Over there.

389
00:23:51,070 --> 00:23:53,250
Although it looks desolate here, planting

390
00:23:53,250 --> 00:23:58,940
mulberry trees here will produce big harvests.

391
00:23:58,940 --> 00:24:00,890
I wanted to plant mulberry trees.

392
00:24:00,890 --> 00:24:04,030
So I bought the land in two hundred bags of rice.

393
00:24:04,030 --> 00:24:07,220
I didn’t expect there to have a lotte world.

394
00:24:10,400 --> 00:24:13,060
There. And there.

395
00:24:13,060 --> 00:24:16,150
People who worked for the government

396
00:24:16,150 --> 00:24:20,850
said something wrong to the King and got fired.

397
00:24:20,850 --> 00:24:23,470
So he reluctantly decided to sell the land.

398
00:24:23,470 --> 00:24:26,020
Really, really, really urgent sale!

399
00:24:26,020 --> 00:24:29,890
I wanted to build a pavilion in a scenic spot.
So I bought that pear garden,

400
00:24:29,890 --> 00:24:33,060
where the Apgujeong Apartment is now.

401
00:24:33,060 --> 00:24:36,740
At that time, Kangnam did not belong to Hanyang,

402
00:24:36,740 --> 00:24:42,340
so the land price was naturally very cheap,
which couldn’t be compared to the Kangbuk.

403
00:24:42,340 --> 00:24:44,390
So was Samsung-dong.

404
00:24:44,390 --> 00:24:50,540
At that time, it was divided into fengen village,
wu tong village and grkshe village.

405
00:24:50,540 --> 00:24:55,200
But there were not more than
two hundred people living there.

406
00:24:56,190 --> 00:24:58,050
It was absolutely a desolate place.

407
00:24:58,050 --> 00:24:59,960
A wasteland of wastelands.

408
00:24:59,960 --> 00:25:04,280
Anyone who lived there at the time would think
it a miracle when sees the Samsung-dong now.

409
00:25:04,280 --> 00:25:05,720
It's completely groundbreaking.

410
00:25:05,720 --> 00:25:08,620
What did my ancestors do?

411
00:25:08,620 --> 00:25:11,390
Why didn’t they buy some lands as well?

412
00:25:11,390 --> 00:25:13,770
Let’s deal with these properties step by step.

413
00:25:13,770 --> 00:25:15,970
The antiques and artwork

414
00:25:15,970 --> 00:25:19,970
will be taken out when I get back.

415
00:25:19,970 --> 00:25:24,380
So many expensive items will arouse suspicion.

416
00:25:24,380 --> 00:25:26,940
OK. I got it.

417
00:25:27,660 --> 00:25:32,120
But, now we start to sort them out.

418
00:25:32,120 --> 00:25:36,960
It makes me really feel that you are leaving here.

419
00:25:36,960 --> 00:25:42,180
To me, I have been waiting for over 400 years.

420
00:25:42,180 --> 00:25:44,610
I thought I was well prepared to leave.

421
00:25:44,610 --> 00:25:48,790
I could leave without anything to miss.

422
00:25:49,620 --> 00:25:50,710
What about now?

423
00:25:50,710 --> 00:25:53,560
I’m running out of time.

424
00:25:53,560 --> 00:25:56,880
But there is still a person,

425
00:25:56,880 --> 00:26:03,480
and the unsettled confusions and feelings.

426
00:26:03,480 --> 00:26:07,890
The strange situation, similar to 400 years ago,

427
00:26:07,890 --> 00:26:09,480
frightens me.

428
00:26:12,140 --> 00:26:17,990
I used to believe that death could be an end.

429
00:26:20,650 --> 00:26:22,570
It doesn’t seem like that now.

430
00:26:28,890 --> 00:26:31,460
Buy a cell phone if you can.

431
00:26:31,460 --> 00:26:33,780
I can’t reach you in an emergency.

432
00:26:36,510 --> 00:26:40,270
Did the person I thought had disappeared forever

433
00:26:40,270 --> 00:26:46,630
reappears in front of me after a long time?

434
00:26:53,120 --> 00:26:54,270
Here you are.

435
00:26:55,070 --> 00:26:59,450
I've never seen any volunteers
on time every week like you.

436
00:26:59,450 --> 00:27:03,330
Volunteering here is the happiest thing I can do.

437
00:27:03,330 --> 00:27:04,720
Why don’t I come to do that?

438
00:27:04,720 --> 00:27:08,320
A rich boy volunteers at a pet rescue center.

439
00:27:08,320 --> 00:27:12,600
If the reporters know this, it's gonna be
a big news, but you won't let me tell.

440
00:27:14,670 --> 00:27:15,810
What’s wrong with that little guy?

441
00:27:15,810 --> 00:27:18,070
He was dumped on the highway.

442
00:27:18,070 --> 00:27:19,290
Distemper.

443
00:27:19,290 --> 00:27:21,480
Hard plantar disease. And red rash is obvious.

444
00:27:21,480 --> 00:27:22,530
What about the diagnostic test?

445
00:27:22,530 --> 00:27:24,000
Positive reaction.

446
00:27:24,000 --> 00:27:27,270
The same goes for blood tests.
Both lymphocytes and neutrophils are high.

447
00:27:27,270 --> 00:27:31,750
X-ray examination revealed pulmonary sclerosis
caused by bronchopneumonia.

448
00:27:31,750 --> 00:27:34,780
The central nervous system can’t be saved either.

449
00:27:34,780 --> 00:27:37,610
We can only do euthanasia now?

450
00:27:37,610 --> 00:27:38,650
Yes.

451
00:27:38,650 --> 00:27:40,240
It should be done tonight.

452
00:27:40,240 --> 00:27:41,770
With magnesium sulfate?

453
00:27:41,770 --> 00:27:43,290
Anesthesia first.

454
00:27:44,530 --> 00:27:48,770
By the way, these days they use propofol.

455
00:27:48,770 --> 00:27:51,330
Many celebrities got into troubles because of it.

456
00:27:51,330 --> 00:27:52,490
Yes.

457
00:27:53,050 --> 00:27:54,280
Let me.

458
00:27:58,510 --> 00:28:00,090
Do you want some papaya tea?

459
00:28:02,220 --> 00:28:04,000
Later,

460
00:28:05,410 --> 00:28:07,500
your pain

461
00:28:10,000 --> 00:28:11,630
will be over.

462
00:28:16,470 --> 00:28:18,100
Goodness!

463
00:28:19,010 --> 00:28:21,900
It’s not my birthday today. Why bother?

464
00:28:21,900 --> 00:28:24,030
It was also the hardest day you ever had.

465
00:28:27,460 --> 00:28:28,600
That’s right.

466
00:28:30,060 --> 00:28:34,790
She already had a bad temper when in my stomach.
I suffered a lot.

467
00:28:35,940 --> 00:28:38,440
What are you going to do with Song-yi?

468
00:28:38,440 --> 00:28:41,460
She has no work now. She is totally free.

469
00:28:41,460 --> 00:28:43,110
I want to have dinner together with her.

470
00:28:43,110 --> 00:28:45,870
You can have dinner every day.

471
00:28:45,870 --> 00:28:49,260
Forget this. Do something special.

472
00:28:49,260 --> 00:28:51,820
Just, special…

473
00:28:53,220 --> 00:28:56,280
Let me give you a hint.

474
00:28:59,400 --> 00:29:02,610
I have a very important thing to do.

475
00:29:02,610 --> 00:29:04,580
So, can I take paid vacation?

476
00:29:04,580 --> 00:29:05,640
Paid vacation?

477
00:29:07,610 --> 00:29:10,000
Sure, of course.

478
00:29:10,000 --> 00:29:11,710
I’m sorry.

479
00:29:11,710 --> 00:29:14,600
I promised to sign the contract at 3 o 'clock.

480
00:29:14,600 --> 00:29:16,050
Come on. It’s OK.

481
00:29:16,050 --> 00:29:17,450
Just leave it to us.

482
00:29:18,950 --> 00:29:21,120
Because it’s my first time to work on that.

483
00:29:21,120 --> 00:29:23,680
I really want to see it myself.

484
00:29:25,750 --> 00:29:27,510
See it?

485
00:29:29,610 --> 00:29:31,280
How about… we delay it?

486
00:29:34,320 --> 00:29:35,610
The customers are from England.

487
00:29:35,610 --> 00:29:37,710
Their schedule says it can only be today.

488
00:29:39,140 --> 00:29:40,750
Then ask them to fly here again next time.

489
00:29:40,750 --> 00:29:42,890
It will just cost them 12 hours.

490
00:29:43,970 --> 00:29:46,480
We’ll delay it so that you can see it next time.

491
00:29:46,480 --> 00:29:48,160
Can that work?

492
00:29:49,090 --> 00:29:50,410
Thank you.

493
00:30:09,380 --> 00:30:12,380
4 P.M. Final exam. Must be present.

494
00:30:12,380 --> 00:30:14,750
If not, you will get an F.

495
00:30:19,880 --> 00:30:24,060
Look at the handwriting. What a boring guy.

496
00:30:29,430 --> 00:30:32,130
Cheon Song-yi! Happy birthday!

497
00:30:32,130 --> 00:30:34,370
Don’t forget to leave your night to me.

498
00:30:41,330 --> 00:30:42,800
You brat.

499
00:30:42,800 --> 00:30:45,370
Don’t you remember it’s my birthday today?

500
00:30:45,370 --> 00:30:46,610
How have you been?

501
00:30:46,610 --> 00:30:47,690
Great, of course.

502
00:30:47,690 --> 00:30:50,010
Mom said you were rejected by all companies.

503
00:30:50,010 --> 00:30:51,320
Are you kidding me?

504
00:30:51,320 --> 00:30:55,360
Just now, someone begged me to be present.

505
00:30:55,360 --> 00:30:57,100
So, I can only agree.

506
00:30:57,100 --> 00:30:59,940
I had no choice but to do them a favor.

507
00:30:59,940 --> 00:31:02,360
Didn’t you break up with your agency?

508
00:31:02,360 --> 00:31:03,360
Can you go out alone?

509
00:31:03,360 --> 00:31:04,490
Of course.

510
00:31:04,490 --> 00:31:08,370
With car and license, where can’t I go?

511
00:31:11,210 --> 00:31:14,640
My cutie, it’s been a while.

512
00:31:33,180 --> 00:31:36,490
Hello, guys! I’m Cheon Song-yi.

513
00:31:37,390 --> 00:31:42,520
This is really a big welcome.

514
00:31:44,130 --> 00:31:47,160
Fine. I haven’t been outside for a long time.

515
00:31:47,160 --> 00:31:48,900
Can you guys drive?

516
00:31:48,900 --> 00:31:50,830
Don't fool around if you can't drive.

517
00:31:50,830 --> 00:31:53,100
Right? My cutie.

518
00:31:54,200 --> 00:31:59,470
Oh, my cutie wants some food. Mommy.

519
00:32:06,420 --> 00:32:07,620
Refuel for me.

520
00:32:07,620 --> 00:32:09,250
Gasoline or diesel?

521
00:32:09,250 --> 00:32:13,120
Refuel for me. Fill up.

522
00:32:13,660 --> 00:32:14,820
Oh, my god!

523
00:32:15,790 --> 00:32:16,890
My bag!

524
00:32:16,890 --> 00:32:19,130
Where is my bag?

525
00:32:19,130 --> 00:32:22,330
I remember I brought it with me. Where is it?

526
00:32:25,300 --> 00:32:26,400
Your bag.

527
00:32:28,670 --> 00:32:29,970
Oops.

528
00:32:29,970 --> 00:32:31,510
Thanks.

