We are now at Cheon Song-yi’s door.

542
00:34:15,639 --> 00:34:17,510
[Cheon Song-yi’s residence interview]

543
00:34:23,989 --> 00:34:26,389
Sorry that I accidentally hit your car.

544
00:34:26,389 --> 00:34:28,060
Please get off the car.

545
00:34:28,060 --> 00:34:29,860
It’s OK. You can just leave.

546
00:34:29,860 --> 00:34:32,690
I can’t just leave. Your car looks expensive.

547
00:34:33,800 --> 00:34:36,159
Please roll down the window first.

548
00:34:36,159 --> 00:34:37,330
I said it’s OK.

549
00:34:37,330 --> 00:34:38,570
The car is not expensive at all.

550
00:34:38,570 --> 00:34:39,940
Just leave.

551
00:34:40,199 --> 00:34:44,710
Well, but it’s still an accident after all.

552
00:34:44,739 --> 00:34:45,710
[GBS News]

553
00:34:45,340 --> 00:34:47,679
Please get off and have a check, OK?

554
00:34:47,679 --> 00:34:53,580
-Miss Cheon Song-yi…
-Isn’t this Cheon Song-yi?

555
00:34:54,150 --> 00:34:56,949
-Please come out for an interview.
-Please look over here.

556
00:34:56,949 --> 00:34:59,590
Please look here.

557
00:35:27,850 --> 00:35:29,850
Miss Cheon, please get off from the car.

558
00:35:29,850 --> 00:35:32,320
-How long are you going to hide?
-You have to check.

559
00:35:35,260 --> 00:35:41,330
You need to confirm the accident. Come out.

560
00:35:41,330 --> 00:35:43,400
Come on. Open the door.

561
00:35:48,400 --> 00:35:50,610
Stop hiding. Come out.

562
00:35:50,610 --> 00:35:52,640
It’s been an hour.

563
00:35:52,640 --> 00:35:54,910
You are making us embarrassed.

564
00:35:54,910 --> 00:35:59,310
In a traffic accident, both parties
have the obligation to confirm together.

565
00:35:59,310 --> 00:36:02,850
I’ll have to force you out if you don’t.

566
00:36:13,360 --> 00:36:16,300
It’s not an accident. You did that on purpose.

567
00:36:17,800 --> 00:36:22,700
You knew someone is in the car,
and you knew the people would get hurt.

568
00:36:22,700 --> 00:36:24,740
But you still hit it on purpose.

569
00:36:24,740 --> 00:36:28,610
So, it’s an intentional injury.

570
00:36:28,610 --> 00:36:30,310
Who are you?

571
00:36:30,950 --> 00:36:33,280
I’m the legal representative of Cheon Song-yi.

572
00:36:34,750 --> 00:36:36,850
Also, the witness to the accident.

573
00:36:39,650 --> 00:36:43,160
If the woman in the car is slightly injured,

574
00:36:43,160 --> 00:36:46,190
that's assault and battery.

575
00:36:46,190 --> 00:36:49,660
You will get 7 to 10 years in prison,
lose your license,

576
00:36:49,660 --> 00:36:52,470
or be fined up to 10 million.

577
00:36:53,740 --> 00:36:55,540
Wait, I…

578
00:36:55,540 --> 00:36:57,970
I just want her to come out to settle it down.

579
00:36:57,970 --> 00:36:58,440
I didn’t want to…

580
00:36:58,440 --> 00:37:02,110
She didn’t want to get out of the car,
but you raised voice to force her out,

581
00:37:02,110 --> 00:37:03,680
making a threatening behavior.

582
00:37:03,680 --> 00:37:07,680
According to article 283 of the criminal code,
it’s the crime of intimidation.

583
00:37:07,680 --> 00:37:09,250
You will be sentenced with less than 3 years,

584
00:37:09,250 --> 00:37:14,460
fined with less than 5 million. Detention or fine.

585
00:37:14,460 --> 00:37:16,390
In this situation,

586
00:37:16,390 --> 00:37:18,530
you can be treated as an active offender.

587
00:37:18,530 --> 00:37:21,800
Do you want me to call the police?

588
00:37:26,170 --> 00:37:28,400
You can take photos.

589
00:37:28,400 --> 00:37:30,710
But if you spread it without permission,

590
00:37:30,710 --> 00:37:32,910
we can sue you for civil damages.

591
00:37:32,910 --> 00:37:36,750
-What the heck?
-What’s going on?

592
00:37:41,720 --> 00:37:44,250
Get off. It’s OK.

593
00:38:04,610 --> 00:38:09,380
You may hide when you do wrong, but not now.

594
00:38:12,010 --> 00:38:13,420
-Who is he?
-Who is he?

595
00:38:13,420 --> 00:38:14,750
Where have you been? Why are you so late,

596
00:38:14,750 --> 00:38:16,490
Manager Do?

597
00:38:17,890 --> 00:38:19,650
Let’s go.

598
00:38:20,520 --> 00:38:22,520
Manager Do.

599
00:38:23,360 --> 00:38:25,590
What?

600
00:38:25,590 --> 00:38:27,760
Hey, take pictures now.

601
00:38:29,130 --> 00:38:30,930
What’s wrong with it?

602
00:38:30,930 --> 00:38:32,030
Is it out of work?

603
00:38:32,030 --> 00:38:33,900
Battery died? What’s going on?

604
00:38:33,900 --> 00:38:35,170
I can’t take pictures now.

605
00:38:35,170 --> 00:38:37,240
I can’t as well.

606
00:38:38,910 --> 00:38:41,610
This is not the way to the classroom.

607
00:38:41,610 --> 00:38:43,310
Don’t I need to take the exam?

608
00:38:43,310 --> 00:38:46,110
It’s already over.

609
00:38:46,110 --> 00:38:47,880
Then, where are we going?

610
00:38:49,750 --> 00:38:51,690
Where is it?

611
00:38:51,690 --> 00:38:53,320
Museum.

612
00:38:53,320 --> 00:38:56,430
The quietest place in school.

613
00:38:56,890 --> 00:38:59,560
I have to thank you for that just now.

614
00:38:59,560 --> 00:39:01,600
But, did you major in law?

615
00:39:01,600 --> 00:39:03,970
You know laws so well.

616
00:39:04,670 --> 00:39:06,840
But I failed to take the exam today.

617
00:39:06,840 --> 00:39:07,540
You saw that just now.

618
00:39:07,540 --> 00:39:09,540
I had no choice. So, forgive me this time.

619
00:39:09,540 --> 00:39:11,610
You would only get F even if you were present.

620
00:39:11,610 --> 00:39:13,080
You were always absent in classes.

621
00:39:13,080 --> 00:39:14,480
Then why are you bossing me around

622
00:39:14,480 --> 00:39:16,240
and making me so embarrassed…

623
00:39:16,240 --> 00:39:17,950
This is the museum.

624
00:39:17,950 --> 00:39:19,680
Come on.

625
00:39:19,680 --> 00:39:22,850
I hate art galleries and museums the most.

626
00:39:22,850 --> 00:39:25,020
It takes only 30 seconds to feel sleepy here.

627
00:39:25,020 --> 00:39:27,920
Why do you take me here…

628
00:39:54,050 --> 00:39:56,020
Seo.

629
00:39:58,990 --> 00:40:02,290
You must be tired by staying up the whole night.

630
00:40:56,910 --> 00:40:58,850
[To Hee-kyung]

631
00:41:06,050 --> 00:41:08,090
Merry Christmas, Song-yi.

632
00:41:08,090 --> 00:41:10,090
Why are you here again?

633
00:41:10,090 --> 00:41:12,730
Stay away from me!

634
00:41:14,130 --> 00:41:15,700
Song-yi!

635
00:42:29,540 --> 00:42:31,640
Hi, Hee-kyung.

636
00:42:31,910 --> 00:42:32,870
Are you on the way here?

637
00:42:32,870 --> 00:42:35,540
But, why are you at the park at this hour?

638
00:42:35,540 --> 00:42:40,350
You're not going to surprise me there, are you?

639
00:42:38,950 --> 00:42:39,950
[Cheon Song-yi, I love you]

640
00:42:40,880 --> 00:42:42,620
What I hate more than anything in the world

641
00:42:42,620 --> 00:42:44,520
is the amusement park surprise.

642
00:42:45,320 --> 00:42:47,190
Of course not.

643
00:42:47,190 --> 00:42:50,990
A man used to prepare a thousand roses for me

644
00:42:50,990 --> 00:42:54,560
[“Cheon Song-yi” sounds the same as
“One thousand” in Korean.]

645
00:42:50,990 --> 00:42:54,560
in the amusement park only because of my name.

646
00:42:54,560 --> 00:42:57,670
Do you know that I had to throw the roses into
oversized garbage bag?

647
00:42:57,670 --> 00:43:00,170
The bag was even broken. That jerk.

648
00:43:00,170 --> 00:43:01,340
I was so mad.

649
00:43:01,340 --> 00:43:03,340
Of course I won’t do that.

650
00:43:03,340 --> 00:43:05,610
OK. See you.

651
00:43:05,610 --> 00:43:08,010
See you later.

652
00:43:12,980 --> 00:43:14,580
Here. There. Take them away.

653
00:43:14,580 --> 00:43:15,780
Now.

654
00:43:15,780 --> 00:43:16,350
All of them?

655
00:43:16,350 --> 00:43:17,490
Yes. Now. All of them.

656
00:43:17,490 --> 00:43:19,450
And that banner.

657
00:43:19,450 --> 00:43:20,360
Take it away.

658
00:43:20,360 --> 00:43:21,960
Now, now, now, hurry up.

659
00:43:21,960 --> 00:43:26,130
Flowers, balloons, and the candles.

660
00:43:27,460 --> 00:43:30,130
Thank you for this ride.

661
00:43:30,130 --> 00:43:31,100
By the way,

662
00:43:31,100 --> 00:43:35,000
how many days will it take to get the car fixed?

663
00:43:35,000 --> 00:43:37,310
I need to call Beom to ask…

664
00:43:38,110 --> 00:43:41,640
He is no longer my manager.

665
00:43:42,910 --> 00:43:45,110
This semester is over. What are you going to do?

666
00:43:45,110 --> 00:43:47,120
Do you want to have the second job?

667
00:43:47,120 --> 00:43:48,480
What?

668
00:43:48,480 --> 00:43:52,350
Like a part-time job in holidays.

669
00:43:52,350 --> 00:43:53,660
How about to be my manager?

670
00:43:53,660 --> 00:43:55,920
-Don’t make nonsense.
-What’s wrong?

671
00:43:55,920 --> 00:43:57,360
Don’t you like to be a manager?

672
00:43:57,360 --> 00:43:58,860
It’s so cool to be called

673
00:43:58,860 --> 00:44:01,060
legal representative.

674
00:44:01,060 --> 00:44:02,300
If you don’t like that,

675
00:44:02,300 --> 00:44:04,570
how about bodyguard?

676
00:44:06,300 --> 00:44:08,340
Pff.

677
00:44:09,270 --> 00:44:12,570
I don't know how to do anything myself.

678
00:44:12,570 --> 00:44:14,840
From the age of 12 to now

679
00:44:14,840 --> 00:44:16,550
I have always been doing what I’m asked

680
00:44:16,550 --> 00:44:18,210
to do in front of the cameras.

681
00:44:18,210 --> 00:44:20,480
That’s all I have done.

682
00:44:20,480 --> 00:44:23,750
I've never done anything with my own hands.

683
00:44:23,750 --> 00:44:26,020
I like coffee so much.

684
00:44:26,020 --> 00:44:29,220
But after I lost my manager, I haven’t
even had coffee recently

685
00:44:29,220 --> 00:44:31,630
because I don’t know how to order.

686
00:44:31,630 --> 00:44:33,460
How much is it?

687
00:44:33,460 --> 00:44:34,230
Coffee?

688
00:44:34,230 --> 00:44:35,200
No.

689
00:44:35,200 --> 00:44:36,970
The job.

690
00:44:36,970 --> 00:44:39,430
Don’t you want me to work for you?

691
00:44:50,350 --> 00:44:52,310
That brat…

692
00:44:52,310 --> 00:44:54,880
Who does he think he is?

693
00:44:58,150 --> 00:45:00,020
Why do you come together?

694
00:45:00,020 --> 00:45:02,920
Well, we met some trouble before.

695
00:45:02,920 --> 00:45:05,560
Since you are here, enjoy the dinner with us.

696
00:45:05,560 --> 00:45:07,730
What dinner?

697
00:45:07,730 --> 00:45:09,700
Alright, you can leave now.

698
00:45:09,700 --> 00:45:11,030
Hey, you…

699
00:45:11,030 --> 00:45:13,140
Don’t hang out too late.

700
00:45:13,140 --> 00:45:14,940
Send her back home when it’s over.

701
00:45:14,940 --> 00:45:16,670
I know.

702
00:45:18,870 --> 00:45:21,140
Why are you bossing me around?

703
00:45:21,140 --> 00:45:24,410
I can see to it myself.

704
00:45:33,560 --> 00:45:37,190
Why is no one else here?

705
00:45:37,190 --> 00:45:38,930
You didn’t rent the whole amusement park

706
00:45:38,930 --> 00:45:40,560
for tonight, did you?

707
00:45:40,560 --> 00:45:42,300
I didn’t!

708
00:45:42,300 --> 00:45:44,470
It’s too much for me

709
00:45:44,470 --> 00:45:46,230
no matter how rich I am.

710
00:45:46,230 --> 00:45:47,870
Maybe because it’s so cold today.

711
00:45:47,870 --> 00:45:50,110
There really aren't many people here.

712
00:45:50,110 --> 00:45:51,770
Then, why did you call me here?

713
00:45:51,770 --> 00:45:56,710
Well, there.

714
00:46:03,920 --> 00:46:05,420
Didn't you say that you would come and

715
00:46:05,420 --> 00:46:09,830
play that every birthday when you were a kid?

716
00:46:13,230 --> 00:46:14,700
It’s moving!

717
00:46:14,700 --> 00:46:16,800
It’s moving!

718
00:46:16,800 --> 00:46:18,870
-Is this really that exciting?
-Yes!

719
00:46:18,870 --> 00:46:22,000
I feel like a star every time I’m on this.

720
00:46:22,000 --> 00:46:25,470
I can see everything from here.

721
00:46:25,670 --> 00:46:27,940
You can’t even sleep for your work.

722
00:46:27,940 --> 00:46:30,310
Are you really OK to be busy like that?

723
00:46:30,310 --> 00:46:31,950
You can stop your job if you don’t want to.

724
00:46:31,950 --> 00:46:33,180
I will tell your mom…

725
00:46:33,180 --> 00:46:34,220
It’s OK.

726
00:46:34,220 --> 00:46:35,720
I’m happy to do that.

727
00:46:35,720 --> 00:46:37,950
If I can’t make money,

728
00:46:37,950 --> 00:46:40,620
mom won’t be angry to you again like before.

729
00:46:40,620 --> 00:46:43,930
My girl, don’t worry about money.

730
00:46:43,930 --> 00:46:45,860
I’ll deal with that myself.

731
00:46:45,860 --> 00:46:47,930
If you are tired, just quit the job.

732
00:46:47,930 --> 00:46:49,460
Don’t say that.

733
00:46:49,460 --> 00:46:51,270
I think it’s interesting.

734
00:46:51,270 --> 00:46:55,100
I can see many celebrities in TV station.

735
00:46:55,100 --> 00:46:57,310
Last time I saw Won Bin! Won Bin!

736
00:46:57,310 --> 00:46:59,810
The man in Autumn Fairy Tale! Dad, you know?

737
00:46:59,810 --> 00:47:02,480
He is so handsome!

738
00:47:02,880 --> 00:47:05,310
Won Bin and I, who is more handsome?

739
00:47:05,310 --> 00:47:08,050
Dad,

740
00:47:08,050 --> 00:47:09,820
even if I’m your daughter,

741
00:47:09,820 --> 00:47:12,320
I can’t lie this time.

742
00:47:12,320 --> 00:47:14,390
Hey.

743
00:47:14,390 --> 00:47:15,590
Do you dare to answer?

744
00:47:15,590 --> 00:47:16,630
Who is more handsome?

745
00:47:16,630 --> 00:47:17,460
Who?

746
00:47:17,460 --> 00:47:20,760
Dad, it’s you!

747
00:47:27,900 --> 00:47:29,970
Yes.

748
00:47:29,970 --> 00:47:31,910
I always came to play that on every birthday

749
00:47:31,910 --> 00:47:33,410
with my dad.

750
00:47:33,410 --> 00:47:36,140
But, how did you know that?

751
00:47:39,150 --> 00:47:42,950
Of course I know everything of you.

752
00:47:43,590 --> 00:47:45,520
Let’s go.

753
00:48:23,930 --> 00:48:26,260
This…

754
00:48:27,300 --> 00:48:30,970
What's wrong with me?

755
00:48:31,670 --> 00:48:38,040
Why do I feel so sad when I see this?

756
00:48:54,660 --> 00:48:59,060
It was like a sad dream.

757
00:48:59,060 --> 00:49:01,360
From now on, it will become the story

758
00:49:01,360 --> 00:49:03,400
like the unreal legend,

759
00:49:03,400 --> 00:49:06,070
like the distant stars.

760
00:49:11,770 --> 00:49:12,940
Lord,

761
00:49:12,940 --> 00:49:16,410
you look pale now.

762
00:49:16,410 --> 00:49:17,910
Catch them!

763
00:49:17,910 --> 00:49:20,350
Go! Go!

764
00:49:42,740 --> 00:49:47,010
My late grandma once said

765
00:49:48,710 --> 00:49:52,810
that it’s better to say goodbye early,

766
00:49:56,490 --> 00:49:58,320
because when it comes to the last moment,

767
00:49:59,550 --> 00:50:04,390
there is no way to say goodbye properly.

768
00:50:08,300 --> 00:50:12,730
Do you remember

769
00:50:13,970 --> 00:50:16,070
what I said to you last time

770
00:50:16,910 --> 00:50:18,640
when the first snow fell?

771
00:50:22,110 --> 00:50:25,050
I want to grow up quickly.

772
00:50:25,050 --> 00:50:30,890
I want you to see me into a beautiful lady.

773
00:50:42,160 --> 00:50:44,370
Before I met you,

774
00:50:45,770 --> 00:50:51,310
I had no hope for the future.

775
00:50:52,470 --> 00:50:56,610
I was full of complaints and despondency.

776
00:51:01,050 --> 00:51:02,680
After I saw you,

777
00:51:04,750 --> 00:51:09,990
I had my first hope for the future,

778
00:51:12,360 --> 00:51:18,270
and wanted to live sincerely.

779
00:51:29,850 --> 00:51:34,780
Thank you. I mean it.

780
00:51:36,920 --> 00:51:41,360
You must return safely to the place

781
00:51:42,520 --> 00:51:44,490
where you were before.

782
00:51:46,530 --> 00:51:48,500
I won’t forget you.

783
00:51:49,100 --> 00:51:51,030
I can’t forget you.

784
00:51:52,800 --> 00:51:57,370
No matter what place I will go to after I die,

785
00:51:59,780 --> 00:52:02,340
I will never forget you.

786
00:52:04,110 --> 00:52:05,610
Catch them!

787
00:52:05,610 --> 00:52:07,280
Catch them!

788
00:52:10,220 --> 00:52:11,550
Catch them!

789
00:52:15,990 --> 00:52:17,530
I want them alive!

790
00:52:29,500 --> 00:52:32,410
He is using witchcraft!

791
00:52:32,410 --> 00:52:33,310
Shoot arrows!

792
00:52:33,310 --> 00:52:34,880
Kill him!

793
00:53:04,670 --> 00:53:07,410
I once wanted time to stop forever.

794
00:53:09,210 --> 00:53:12,880
The moment when my loved one died.

795
00:53:27,500 --> 00:53:31,430
Don't want to see. Don't want to believe.

796
00:53:32,200 --> 00:53:34,170
I can do nothing.

797
00:53:35,340 --> 00:53:39,880
The moment when I felt so powerless.

798
00:54:26,420 --> 00:54:29,120
I have been restless these days.

799
00:54:30,430 --> 00:54:31,790
Thank you.

800
00:54:32,590 --> 00:54:34,200
I’m happy to be here.

801
00:54:38,370 --> 00:54:40,640
I have prepared to be beaten by you

802
00:54:40,640 --> 00:54:42,070
before I’m going to say the next thing.

803
00:54:44,840 --> 00:54:48,940
I like you to be in the situation like now.

804
00:54:50,880 --> 00:54:53,250
To be honest, I’m happy

805
00:54:54,220 --> 00:54:55,650
that you could be in trouble.

806
00:54:56,220 --> 00:54:57,220
What?

807
00:54:57,220 --> 00:54:59,760
Because finally I can do something for you.

808
00:55:01,090 --> 00:55:03,390
I can get the chance to step into your life.

809
00:55:06,500 --> 00:55:07,860
Am I bad?

810
00:55:08,530 --> 00:55:10,300
Yes.

811
00:55:10,300 --> 00:55:11,800
So bad.

812
00:55:12,300 --> 00:55:13,440
But,

813
00:55:15,040 --> 00:55:18,640
can you regard this as my love to you?

